events.description: Antonius Primus enters Rome to claim the title of Emperor for Nero's former general Vespasian.
events.html: • AD 69 – Antonius Primus enters Rome to claim the title of Emperor for Nero's former general Vespasian.[1]

events.description: Richard I of England is captured and imprisoned by Leopold V of Austria on his way home to England after the Third Crusade.
events.html: • 1192 – Richard I of England is captured and imprisoned by Leopold V of Austria on his way home to England after the Third Crusade.[2]

events.description: Cardinal Jacques Fournier, a Cistercian monk, is elected Pope Benedict XII.
events.html: • 1334 – Cardinal Jacques Fournier, a Cistercian monk, is elected Pope Benedict XII.[3]

events.description: The Louisiana Purchase is completed at a ceremony in New Orleans.
events.html: • 1803 – The Louisiana Purchase is completed at a ceremony in New Orleans.[4]

events.description: Peninsular War: The Siege of Zaragoza begins.
events.html: • 1808 – Peninsular War: The Siege of Zaragoza begins.

events.description: HMS Clio under the command of Captain Onslow arrives at Port Egmont under orders to take possession of the Falkland Islands.
events.html: • 1832 – HMS Clio under the command of Captain Onslow arrives at Port Egmont under orders to take possession of the Falkland Islands.[5]

entities.name: Reassertion of British sovereignty over the Falkland Islands (1833)

events.description: French presidential election: Having won the popular vote in a landslide, Louis Napoleon Bonaparte is inaugurated in the chamber of the National Assembly as the first (and only) president of the French Second Republic.
events.html: • 1848 – French presidential election: Having won the popular vote in a landslide, Louis Napoleon Bonaparte is inaugurated in the chamber of the National Assembly as the first (and only) president of the French Second Republic.[6]

events.description: South Carolina becomes the first state to attempt to secede from the United States with the South Carolina Declaration of Secession.
events.html: • 1860 – South Carolina becomes the first state to attempt to secede from the United States with the South Carolina Declaration of Secession.[7]

events.description: World War I: The last Australian troops are evacuated from Gallipoli.
events.html: • 1915 – World War I: The last Australian troops are evacuated from Gallipoli.

events.description: Cheka, the first Soviet secret police force, is founded.
events.html: • 1917 – Cheka, the first Soviet secret police force, is founded.

events.description: Adolf Hitler is released from Landsberg Prison.
events.html: • 1924 – Adolf Hitler is released from Landsberg Prison.[8]

events.description: Captain America Comics #1, containing the first appearance of the superhero Captain America, is published.
events.html: • 1940 – Captain America Comics #1, containing the first appearance of the superhero Captain America, is published.[9]

events.description: World War II: First battle of the American Volunteer Group, better known as the "Flying Tigers", in Kunming, China.
events.html: • 1941 – World War II: First battle of the American Volunteer Group, better known as the "Flying Tigers", in Kunming, China.

events.description: World War II: Japanese air forces bomb Calcutta, India.
events.html: • 1942 – World War II: Japanese air forces bomb Calcutta, India.

events.description: It's a Wonderful Life premieres at the Globe Theatre in New York to mixed reviews.
events.html: • 1946 – It's a Wonderful Life premieres at the Globe Theatre in New York to mixed reviews. [1]

events.description: An earthquake in Nankaidō, Japan causes a tsunami which kills at least one thousand people and destroys 36,000 homes.
events.html: • 1946 – An earthquake in Nankaidō, Japan causes a tsunami which kills at least one thousand people and destroys 36,000 homes.[10]

events.description: Indonesian National Revolution: The Dutch military captures Yogyakarta, the temporary capital of the newly formed Republic of Indonesia.
events.html: • 1948 – Indonesian National Revolution: The Dutch military captures Yogyakarta, the temporary capital of the newly formed Republic of Indonesia.

events.description: The EBR-1 in Arco, Idaho becomes the first nuclear power plant to generate electricity. The electricity powered four light bulbs.
events.html: • 1951 – The EBR-1 in Arco, Idaho becomes the first nuclear power plant to generate electricity. The electricity powered four light bulbs.

events.description: A United States Air Force C-124 crashes and burns in Moses Lake, Washington, killing 87 of the 115 people on board.
events.html: • 1952 – A United States Air Force C-124 crashes and burns in Moses Lake, Washington, killing 87 of the 115 people on board.[11]

events.description: Cardiff is proclaimed the capital city of Wales, United Kingdom.
events.html: • 1955 – Cardiff is proclaimed the capital city of Wales, United Kingdom.[12]

events.description: The initial production version of the Boeing 707 makes its first flight.
events.html: • 1957 – The initial production version of the Boeing 707 makes its first flight.

events.description: Vietnam War: The National Liberation Front of South Vietnam, popularly known as the Viet Cong, is formally established in Tân Lập village, present day Tây Ninh province.
events.html: • 1960 – Vietnam War: The National Liberation Front of South Vietnam, popularly known as the Viet Cong, is formally established in Tân Lập village, present day Tây Ninh province.[13]

events.description: A Pennsylvania Railroad Budd Metroliner exceeds 249 kilometres per hour (155 mph) on their New York Division, also present-day Amtrak's Northeast Corridor.
events.html: • 1967 – A Pennsylvania Railroad Budd Metroliner exceeds 249 kilometres per hour (155 mph) on their New York Division, also present-day Amtrak's Northeast Corridor.

events.description: The Zodiac Killer murders his first two officially confirmed victims, David Arthur Faraday and Betty Lou Jensen, on Lake Herman Road in Benicia, California, United States.
events.html: • 1968 – The Zodiac Killer murders his first two officially confirmed victims, David Arthur Faraday and Betty Lou Jensen, on Lake Herman Road in Benicia, California, United States.[14]

events.description: Koza riot: After a series of hit-and-runs and other vehicular incidents involving American service personnel, roughly 5,000 Okinawans take to the streets, clashing with American law enforcement in protest against the U.S. occupation of Okinawa.
events.html: • 1970 – Koza riot: After a series of hit-and-runs and other vehicular incidents involving American service personnel, roughly 5,000 Okinawans take to the streets, clashing with American law enforcement in protest against the U.S. occupation of Okinawa.[15]

entities.name: United States Civil Administration of the Ryukyu Islands

events.description: Assassination of Luis Carrero Blanco: A car bomb planted by ETA in Madrid kills three people, including the Prime Minister of Spain, Admiral Luis Carrero Blanco.
events.html: • 1973 – Assassination of Luis Carrero Blanco: A car bomb planted by ETA in Madrid kills three people, including the Prime Minister of Spain, Admiral Luis Carrero Blanco.[16]

events.description: With the approval of the State Council, China’s two largest newspapers, the People’s Daily and the Guangming Daily, publish in full for the first time the Second Chinese Character Simplification Scheme.
events.html: • 1977 – With the approval of the State Council, China’s two largest newspapers, the People’s Daily and the Guangming Daily, publish in full for the first time the Second Chinese Character Simplification Scheme.[17]

entities.name: State Council of the People’s Republic of China
Second round of simplified Chinese characters

events.description: The Summit Tunnel fire, one of the largest transportation tunnel fires in history, burns after a freight train carrying over one million liters of gasoline derails near the town of Todmorden, England, in the Pennines.
events.html: • 1984 – The Summit Tunnel fire, one of the largest transportation tunnel fires in history, burns after a freight train carrying over one million liters of gasoline derails near the town of Todmorden, England, in the Pennines.

events.description: Disappearance of Jonelle Matthews from Greeley, Colorado.  Her remains were discovered on July 23, 2019, located about 24 km (15 mi) southeast of Jonelle's home. The cause of death "was a gunshot wound to the head."
events.html: • 1984 – Disappearance of Jonelle Matthews from Greeley, Colorado. Her remains were discovered on July 23, 2019, located about 24 km (15 mi) southeast of Jonelle's home.[18][19] The cause of death "was a gunshot wound to the head."[20]

entities.name: Disappearance and death of Jonelle Matthews

events.description: Pope John Paul II announces the institution of World Youth Day.
events.html: • 1985 – Pope John Paul II announces the institution of World Youth Day.

events.description: In the worst peacetime sea disaster, the passenger ferry Doña Paz sinks after colliding with the oil tanker MT Vector in the Tablas Strait of the Philippines, killing an estimated 4,000 people (1,749 official).
events.html: • 1987 – In the worst peacetime sea disaster, the passenger ferry Doña Paz sinks after colliding with the oil tanker MT Vector in the Tablas Strait of the Philippines, killing an estimated 4,000 people (1,749 official).

events.description: War on drugs: The United Nations agrees upon and promulgates the United Nations Convention Against Illicit Traffic in Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances, one of three major drug control treaties currently in force.
events.html: • 1988 – War on drugs: The United Nations agrees upon and promulgates the United Nations Convention Against Illicit Traffic in Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances, one of three major drug control treaties currently in force.[21]

entities.name: United Nations Convention Against Illicit Traffic in Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances

events.description: The United States invasion of Panama deposes Manuel Noriega.
events.html: • 1989 – The United States invasion of Panama deposes Manuel Noriega.

events.description: A Missouri court sentences the Palestinian militant Zein Isa and his wife Maria to death for the honor killing of their daughter Palestina.
events.html: • 1991 – A Missouri court sentences the Palestinian militant Zein Isa and his wife Maria to death for the honor killing of their daughter Palestina.

events.description: NATO begins peacekeeping in Bosnia.
events.html: • 1995 – NATO begins peacekeeping in Bosnia.

events.description: American Airlines Flight 965, a Boeing 757, crashes into a mountain 50 km north of Cali, Colombia, killing 159 of the 163 people on board.
events.html: • 1995 – American Airlines Flight 965, a Boeing 757, crashes into a mountain 50 km north of Cali, Colombia, killing 159 of the 163 people on board.[22]

events.description: Macau is handed over to China by Portugal.
events.html: • 1999 – Macau is handed over to China by Portugal.

events.description: A gang of thieves steal £26.5 million worth of currency from the Donegall Square West headquarters of Northern Bank in Belfast, Northern Ireland, United Kingdom, one of the largest bank robberies in British history.
events.html: • 2004 – A gang of thieves steal £26.5 million worth of currency from the Donegall Square West headquarters of Northern Bank in Belfast, Northern Ireland, United Kingdom, one of the largest bank robberies in British history.

events.description: Elizabeth II becomes the oldest monarch in the history of the United Kingdom, surpassing Queen Victoria, who lived for 81 years and 243 days.
events.html: • 2007 – Elizabeth II becomes the oldest monarch in the history of the United Kingdom, surpassing Queen Victoria, who lived for 81 years and 243 days.[23]

events.description: The Portrait of Suzanne Bloch (1904), by the Spanish artist Pablo Picasso, and O Lavrador de Café by Brazilian modernist painter Cândido Portinari, are stolen from the São Paulo Museum of Art in Brazil. Both will be recovered a few weeks later.
events.html: • 2007 – The Portrait of Suzanne Bloch (1904), by the Spanish artist Pablo Picasso, and O Lavrador de Café by Brazilian modernist painter Cândido Portinari, are stolen from the São Paulo Museum of Art in Brazil. Both will be recovered a few weeks later.[24]

events.description: The United States Space Force becomes the first new branch of the United States Armed Forces since 1947.
events.html: • 2019 – The United States Space Force becomes the first new branch of the United States Armed Forces since 1947.[25]
